description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;University Hospitals Birmingham NHS Foundation Trust (UHB)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Department of General Surgery and Gastroenterology&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Research Fellow in General Surgery&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Post&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications are invited for a Research Fellow in General Surgery at Good Hope Hospital. The post will commenceas soon as possibleand will be for 12 months in the first instance, extendable to 2 years. The post is suitable for a surgical trainee pre or post MRCS. The post-holder will carry out a lab-based MD/PhD degree in Peritoneal Malignancy, based at the University of Birmingham, under joint supervision of Professor Andrew Beggs and Mr Haney Youssef. This post provides opportunity for a trainee who has completed their basic surgical training (BST) to undertake a period of structured academic research whilst maintaining their surgical skills through undertaking ‘SHO’ level on-calls. There is also the opportunity to be involved in clinical research and to learn clinical research methods. You may be required to work cross-site.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;University Hospitals, Birmingham (UHB) has healthcare facilities at multiple sites. This includes Queen Elizabeth hospital, Heartlands hospital, Good Hope Hospital, Solihull Hospitals, Birmingham Chest Clinic and other healthcare facilities. The University Hospitals, Birmingham (HGS) is delivering services on three sites namely Birmingham Heartlands Hospital, Good Hope Hospital &amp; Solihull Hospital. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to Get More Information&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are interested in this post and wish to have an informal discussion regarding the role please do not hesitate to contact Mr Haney Youssef, Consultant Colorectal Surgeon on 0121 424 9387, Haney.Youssef@uhb.nhs.uk or Professor Andrew Beggs on a.beggs@bham.ac.uk. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to apply&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;All applications must be made via the NHS Jobs website, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;should you have any difficulty in applying please contact the Medical Workforce Team on 0121 424 8993,option 4 and option 1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Job Reference: 295-MC-40627&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
